HEADWORD: Gyle
<hw>Gyle</hw> <pr>(g⟦imac⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>guiller</ets> to ferment. Cf. <er>Guillevat</er>.]</ety>
<def>Fermented wort used for making vinegar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Gyle tun</b></col> <fld>(Brewing)</fld>, <cd>a large vat
in which wort ferments.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gymnadeniopsis</ent>⟦br⟧
